Maintainer: Stephen Salerno <ssalerno@fredhutch.org>
Description: R package to estimate population average controlled difference (ACD), or under stronger assumptions, the population average treatment effect (PATE), for a given outcome between levels of a binary treatment, exposure, or other group membership variable of interest for clustered, stratified survey samples where sample selection depends on the comparison group.
